This paper deals with the parallel solution of large linear systems, which is a common problem in scientific computing. The paper specifically focuses on pipelined Krylov subspace solvers, which are used to improve scalability on distributed memory machines. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SC (Scientific Computing), and cs.MS (Mathematical Software).
